<dl id="un1013bi"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="un1" href="#un1013">UN1: </a>  <a href="../../ff/unbs/un1all.htm#un1013bi"> (NLI.3) 13(bi)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> (sacral <font color="green">[sketch of symbol]</font> orangefiery, <small>Not cancelled</small></blockquote> <dd class="well"> <ul class="list-inline" id="un1013bi"><li>Ulysses </li><li><a href="../../ulex/n/lexn.htm#un1013bi">2021</a> </li><li><a href="../../ulex/n/n86.htm#un1013bi">2017</a> </li><li><a href="../../ulex/n/n86.htm#un1013bi">1986 (12.343f)</a> </li><li><a href="../../ulex/n/l22n.htm#un1013bi">1922</a> </li><li><ms href="#un1013bi">MS V.A.8-5v</ms> </li><li>JJA 13:094 </li><li><a name="n1B1d" href="../udra/u12da.htm#n1b1d">Usage</a> </li><li><a href="../../ulex/n/n1b1d.htm#un1013bi">Draft: 12B.1</a></li> </ul> <blockquote class="sources">The first centre, at the base of the spine, so arranges its undulations as to give the effect of its being divided into quadrants, with hollows between them. This makes it seem as though marked with the sign of the cross, and for that reason the cross is often used to symbolise this centre, and sometimes a flaming cross is used to indicate the serpent-fire which resides in it. When aroused into full activity <mark>this centre is fiery orange-red</mark> in colour. <small> <a name="THmay1910" href="/udra/udex.htm#thmay1910"><cite title="source">The Theosophist</cite></a> (May 1910), C.W. Leadbeater, &ldquo;FORCE-CENTRES AND THE SERPENT-FIRE&rdquo; p. 1077</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Note: Possibly copied to missing notesheet.  <br>Raphael transcription: <a name="c07259g" href="../../../f/ff/fnbs/c07all.htm#c07259g">VI.C.07:259(g)</a> </mm></dd> </dd></dl>
